That's according to United Nations Children's Fund Regional Director for the Middle East, Geert Cappelaere. He says are still close to two-hundred thousand children trapped in the enclave, as fierce fighting continues. According to news reports, as many as fifty thousand civilians have fled offensives against rebel forces in recent days in east Ghouta and in the northern town of Afrin. Cappelaere says it is "never too late" to start upholding the "sacred principle" of child protection there...
